  "prompt": "How do junk yards make money?",
  "response": "Junk yards, also known as salvage yards or scrapyards, make money through several revenue streams:\n\n1. Selling used auto parts\n- Removing and reselling functional parts from vehicles\n- Selling parts at lower prices than new replacement parts\n\n2. Scrap metal recycling\n- Selling metal components by weight to recycling facilities\n- Metals like steel, aluminum, copper, and brass have market value\n\n3. Vehicle purchase\n- Buying old, damaged, or non-functional vehicles\n- Paying owners for cars based on weight and salvageable parts\n\n4. Sales of entire salvaged vehicles\n- Selling complete vehicles that can be repaired or used for parts\n\n5. Core charges\n- Charging a deposit for certain parts that can be rebuilt or remanufactured\n- Refunding the deposit when customers return the old part\n\n6. Environmental fees\n- Charging for proper disposal of hazardous materials\n- Recycling fluids, batteries, and other components\n\n7. Wholesale parts sales\n- Selling parts in bulk to auto repair shops, mechanics, and other businesses\n\n8. Online sales\n- Selling parts through websites and online marketplaces\n\nThe key to profitability is efficiently processing vehicles, maximizing the value of salvageable parts, and minimizing disposal costs.",
